  "doc_id": "32197",
  "text": "Bone marrow-derived mesenchymal stem cells (BMSCs) and scaffolds in SCI regeneration. Itosaka and colleagues [CITATION_1] have reported that BMSCs seeded on fibrin scaffold and injected into hemisected rat spinal cord showed an increased survival, as well as an enhanced ability to migrate into the damaged spinal cord, to differentiate in neurons, compared with the BMSCs implanted alone. In addition, they observed a significant improvement of locomotor function at 14, 21 and 28 days after transplantation, according to the Basso-Beattie-Bresnahan (BBB) Loco-motor Rating Scale [CITATION_2] .",
